how_to_log_in: [{"task": "The scribe will receive an email from the customer containing their username and setup instructions.", "owner": "End User", "system": "Onboarding Email", "resources": []}, {"task": "Log in to your Dignity account.", "owner": "End User", "system": "Dignity Account Login", "resources": []}, {"task": "Using Citrix Receiver, log in with username and password at the specified URL.  Activate the account by going to https://password.dignityhealth.org/ and selecting “Activate your New Account” Enter full first name, last name, and DOB (mm/dd) Activate the account by going to https://password.dignityhealth.org/ and selecting “Activate your New Account” Enter full first name, last name, and DOB (mm/dd) Create a New Password Set up challenge questions (security questions) to complete the account setup E-sign the Dignity Network Usage Policy Proceed to set up an OKTA account using https://commonspiritcorp.okta.com/ Download Okta Verify on the personal phone Login into https://commonspiritcorp.okta.com/ using the password created on https://password.dignityhealth.org/ Will get an option to register the phone number Access the Cerner Powerchart site: https://nfuse.dignityhealth.org to sign in with the username received and new password just created/ Enter username and the password created Click on the check box \"I accept the Terms & Conditions\" before clicking \"Log on\" because the option will remain inactive until this box is checked. After clicking on Log on, scribe will need to enter 1 or 2 for the verification code. If 1 is entered, the scribe receives a call on the phone to verify and if 2 is entered, they will receive a prompt on Okta Verify “Yes, It’s Me”or “No, It's Not Me”, scribe has to click on “Yes, It’s Me” In case, the scribe does not receive a call or code, they can enter 0 to abort and try the above step once again", "owner": "End User", "system": "Citrix Access", "resources": ["https://nfuse.dignityhealth.org/citrix/DHEXTGWeb/"]}, {"task": "Once logged in, proceed to access the EHR interface as directed.", "owner": "End User", "system": "EHR Access", "resources": []}]
